description:
The Trigan Empire was a series that began in Fleetway's Ranger comic in September 1965, but when Ranger cancelled in June 1966 with its 40th issue, it was merged into Look and Learn from that title's issue #232. The Trigan Empire continued in Look and Learn until the final issue, #1049, published April 1982. From the first story through until June 1976 Don Lawrence provided the series' art; the volumes below comprise a complete reprint collection of the Don Lawrence era of The Trigan Empire, a set of 12 limited edition hardbacks published by the Don Lawrence Collection, with refurbished artwork. They volumes were printed out of order; e.g. Volume 8: The Prisoner of Zerrs, was the first volume published.

The stories revolve around the planet Elekton where the leader of the Vorg race starts a new empire lead by their king Trigo.
name: Trigan Empire

The 1st volume of reprint anthology Batman Legends published in the UK by Panini. description:
James Palmiotti, Justin Gray and Joseph M. Linsner return to right where their classic “Wolverine & The Black Cat : Claws” storyline left off to bring us an all-new tale of action, intrigue and razor-sharp appendages.

Two of Marvel’s most beloved and be-clawed heroes, Wolverine and Black Cat, have barely had time to catch their breath from defeating the villainous mastermind Arcade and his sidekick White Rabbit when the two evil schemers find an escape from their exile in The Savage Land, and an entryway into revenge! Watch the fur fly as these four fight it out in an all-new, no-holds-barred Claws adventure!

NOTE: Indicia titled as "Wolverine & The Black Cat: Claws 2".

description:
FEAR ITSELF TIE-IN! Amidst the unstoppable force of FEAR ITSELF tearing through New York City, Wolverine and his girlfriend, Melita Garner, find themselves having to make hard decisions in order to do what they do best. The British intelligence turned mercenary black ops group STRIKE has taken advantage of the chaos and activated sleeper agents for one final, deadly mission. It’s up to Wolverine to stop them, but in leaving Melita to report from the ground, will his choice prove fatal?
